who I am." ]

50
00:02:02,620 --> 00:02:04,585
[ "I hope you love my present." ]

51
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:05,815
[ "See you again." ]

52
00:02:05,990 --> 00:02:07,659
I'll play the next song for you.

53
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:11,055
[ It must be the sunny weather.
We got a lot of requests for this song. ]

54
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:13,285
Hey, Ho-rang.

55
00:02:13,490 --> 00:02:14,559
It's...

56
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:15,695
[ Seoyeon High School ]

57
00:02:16,330 --> 00:02:18,069
You're listening, aren't you?

58
00:02:18,070 --> 00:02:19,769
I won't be scared just because you do
things like this.

59
00:02:19,770 --> 00:02:21,939
So, come to me and say it to my face

60
00:02:21,940 --> 00:02:24,265
instead of saying all that nonsense
from behind the keyboard.

61
00:02:36,020 --> 00:02:37,985
[ I was so shocked when I heard it. ]

62
00:02:38,090 --> 00:02:40,385
Is this one of your pranks? Is that it?

63
00:02:41,620 --> 00:02:44,225
Answer me! You punk!

64
00:02:44,990 --> 00:02:47,825
- My gosh, sir.
- That's admirable.

65
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:51,465
Please continue to work harder

66
00:02:51,570 --> 00:02:55,335
for our school, Seoyeon High School.

67
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,405
Okay?

68
00:03:01,310 --> 00:03:02,405
Got that?

69
00:03:02,910 --> 00:03:06,209
Do you know how big of a problem
you caused?

70
00:03:06,210 --> 00:03:08,275
Do you know that? You punk.

71
00:03:08,350 --> 00:03:12,485
How dare you treat this
like some kind of a joke?

72
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:17,159
Hey, you never cause trouble.

73
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:19,685
What happened?
This is a pretty big mess you got there.

74
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:23,125
Since this happened anyway,

75
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:26,625
cut down on the segments
and delegate more to the others.

76
00:03:28,470 --> 00:03:29,769
Are you listening?

77
00:03:29,770 --> 00:03:30,865
Sorry?

78
00:03:31,110 --> 00:03:32,205
I'm sorry.

79
00:03:33,340 --> 00:03:34,505
Think about it.

80
00:03:45,090 --> 00:03:48,585
So you handpicked this awful story?

81
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:51,055
Apologize first.

82
00:03:51,290 --> 00:03:53,155
You caused a lot of trouble
for everyone here.

83
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:57,125
Oh, right. I'm sorry about that.

84
00:03:57,730 --> 00:03:59,225
Now, answer me.

85
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:01,765
All these trashy stories you read.

86
00:04:01,970 --> 00:04:04,135
Are you the one who picked them?

87
00:04:04,540 --> 00:04:08,235
Well, why don't we get going now?

88
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,609
See you later, So-hyun.

89
00:04:09,610 --> 00:04:11,505
- Bye.
- Bye.

90
00:04:17,520 --> 00:04:20,245
Yes. I picked them.

91
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:23,285
What an awful taste.

92
00:04:24,490 --> 00:04:27,059
Hey, So-hyun.
If this is what you're going to do...

93
00:04:27,060 --> 00:04:29,295
I guess you really are hiding something.

94
00:04:30,530 --> 00:04:32,125
- What?
- What is it?

95
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:36,635
What has gotten you so scared like this?

96
00:04:39,870 --> 00:04:41,505
Should I let you in on something?

97
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:43,735
All these years, you've been...

98
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:51,615
So-hyun.

99
00:05:02,230 --> 00:05:03,425
What is this?

100
00:05:05,030 --> 00:05:05,999
What?

101
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,395
Do you think everything
we do here is a joke?

102
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,905
Yes. It seems that way.

103
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:14,175
Did you not know about my temper?

104
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,475
You knew.

105
00:05:16,540 --> 00:05:19,375
You recruited me because you wanted
your club to get some attention. Now what?

106
00:05:20,010 --> 00:05:21,545
Am I useless to your club now?

107
00:05:23,150 --> 00:05:24,715
Then, forget about it.

108
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:31,285
You think
everyone's business is insignificant.

109
00:05:31,460 --> 00:05:33,255
And you think
only yours matters, don't you?

110
00:05:35,930 --> 00:05:37,829
I don't know how famous you are
to blindly throw

111
00:05:37,830 --> 00:05:39,895
a tantrum here. But you know what?

112
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:44,769
- No one will stay by your side.
- What?

113
00:05:44,770 --> 00:05:47,475
You think people are paying attention
to you because of who you are, right?

114
00:05:48,310 --> 00:05:49,604
Don't fool yourself.

115
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:52,745
People just need someone
to focus their attention on.

116
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:54,975
And you just happen to be on their radar.

117
00:05:56,380 --> 00:05:58,485
Do you think people will continue to stay

118
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:01,415
by your side
when you are no longer interesting?

119
00:06:03,660 --> 00:06:04,955
Come to your senses.

120
00:06:05,730 --> 00:06:07,655
If you keep this up,

121
00:06:08,730 --> 00:06:10,325
you'll be alone forever.

122
00:06:13,770 --> 00:06:16,535
Hey, that's what I want to tell you.

123
00:06:16,770 --> 00:06:18,539
You must think you're some hotshot student

124
00:06:18,540 --> 00:06:20,605
if you act all tough and important.

125
00:06:21,580 --> 00:06:23,775
No one will stay by your side.

126
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:26,945
Rot for the rest of your life
in an awful place like this.

127
00:06:28,020 --> 00:06:29,815
No one will pay attention to you.

128
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:35,055
Leave.

129
00:06:36,690 --> 00:06:38,385
You're no longer needed here for good.

130
00:06:50,770 --> 00:06:57,075
[ Story Box ]

131
00:06:58,410 --> 00:07:00,649
Baek Ho-rang is unbelievable.

132
00:07:00,650 --> 00:07:03,119
How could she already cause trouble
when the semester just started?

133
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,619
- Who?
- Ho-rang.

134
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:05,785
Be careful.

135
00:07:05,950 --> 00:07:07,045
There's water here.

136
00:07:08,390 --> 00:07:09,419
- Hey, Woo-jae.
- Yes?

137
00:07:09,420 --> 00:07:12,129
Want to go to the Han River after
the test? There's something I want to try.

138
00:07:12,130 --> 00:07:14,329
I want to pitch a tent at the Han River,
and have ramyeon.

139
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:16,025
- Han River?
- Yes.

140
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:17,299
Actually,

141
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:19,599
should we just study there?

142
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:21,269
What do you think? We could bring a mat.

143
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:23,895
It might be cold if we stay there
for too long.

144
00:07:24,010 --> 00:07:27,505
If it's cold, we can bring padded jackets.

145
00:07:28,010 --> 00:07:29,135
Okay.

146
00:07:29,540 --> 00:07:31,505
- I'll look into it then.
- Okay.

147
00:07:31,910 --> 00:07:34,049
Let's get some gummy snacks
on our way back.

148
00:07:34,050 --> 00:07:35,849
I downloaded the Netflix American drama,

149
00:07:35,850 --> 00:07:37,519
so we can watch it offline.

150
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:39,115
Let's hurry up and go watch it.

151
00:07:41,090 --> 00:07:43,989
I'm sorry.
I agreed to play soccer with the guys.

152
00:07:43,990 --> 00:07:46,589
What do you mean? You agreed to
watch a drama with me during lunch today

153
00:07:46,590 --> 00:07:48,725
when we talked on the phone yesterday.

154
00:07:49,230 --> 00:07:50,399
I made these plans last week.

155
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:53,695
Then you should've told me
on the phone yesterday.

156
00:07:59,410 --> 00:08:01,435
Okay. Call me later then.

157
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:03,839
- Hey, hold on.
- Hey, Kang Jae-yi!

158
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,979
Let's go together.

159
00:08:04,980 --> 00:08:07,375
- Jae-yi, can you do this?
- What is it?

160
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:10,349
- What is that?
- This is the trend.

161
00:08:10,350 --> 00:08:12,645
- What kind of trend is that?
- Why don't you know this?

162
00:08:12,850 --> 00:08:13,945
Let's go.

163
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:22,130
- Hello.
- Hello.

164
00:08:20,390 --> 00:08:22,330
[ Misunderstandings and Conflicts That
Occur Due to Lack of Communication ]

165
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,829
This is Class 1 and 2, right?

166
00:08:23,830 --> 00:08:24,669
- Yes.
- Yes.

167
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:25,999
You were great earlier.

168
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,699
Shut your mouth. I'm in a bad mood.

169
00:08:27,700 --> 00:08:29,339
Is that why you joined
the broadcasting team?

170
00:08:29,340 --> 00:08:30,969
To go after the person who's exposing you?

171
00:08:30,970 --> 00:08:33,665
Your scale is really great.

172
00:08:33,810 --> 00:08:35,339
Hold on.

173
00:08:35,340 --> 00:08:37,905
If you cause trouble like that,
won't So-hyun end up suffering?

174
00:08:37,980 --> 00:08:40,579
- Kim Yu-shin.
- Yes, that's me.

175
00:08:40,580 --> 00:08:42,345
- Let's focus, Yu-shin.
- Okay.

176
00:08:42,550 --> 00:08:44,419
- Kim Ju-hyun.
- You shouldn't hurt

177
00:08:44,420 --> 00:08:46,319
the broadcasting team for your own greed.

178
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,989
- Hey, Kim Yu-shin.
- Yes?

179
00:08:47,990 --> 00:08:50,055
Have you ever gotten hit on the mouth?

180
00:08:51,590 --> 00:08:54,359
And don't talk about the broadcasting team
in front of me again.

181
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:55,329
I quit.

182
00:08:55,330 --> 00:08:56,295
What?

183
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:02,195
- Choi Yun-seok.
- Really? That's incredible.

184
00:09:04,340 --> 00:09:05,405
[ Application to SHBS, Name: Kim Yu-shin ]

185
00:09:05,470 --> 00:09:08,775
Thank you, friend.
This is a gift given to me by the skies.

186
00:09:10,310 --> 00:09:12,105
[ Ji So-hyun ]

187
00:09:13,550 --> 00:09:16,279
But why did you join
if you were going to quit?

188
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:18,315
You were never interested
in anything like that before.

189
00:09:18,590 --> 00:09:20,645
There was something I wanted to find,

190
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,859
but I don't need to anymore.

191
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:24,725
What? What is it?

192
00:09:25,190 --> 00:09:27,285
[ I can do it on my own. ]

193
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,755
[ I can do it. ]

194
00:09:32,170 --> 00:09:34,500
I can't do it.

195
00:09:32,430 --> 00:09:35,635
[ A few days later ]

196
00:09:36,140 --> 00:09:39,465
My gosh. Darn it!

197
00:09:40,740 --> 00:09:43,610
[ Seoyeon High School ]

198
00:09:40,810 --> 00:09:43,679
Why do you always take the bus
when you have so much money?

199
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:46,249
How can I take a taxi to and from
school every day?

200
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:48,715
Why not?
You buy expensive candles all the time.

201
00:09:49,780 --> 00:09:52,689
Ho-rang. Take a look at this.
You know the YouTuber, Melonie, right?

202
00:09:52,690 --> 00:09:54,490
The girl who was accused of
bullying in the past.

203
00:09:52,790 --> 00:09:54,590
[ "Popular YouTuber, Melonie, Admits To
Bullying, 'I Have No Excuses'" ]

204
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:56,589
Gosh, she's really trashy.

205
00:09:56,590 --> 00:09:58,085
I should unsubscribe from her.

206
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:01,699
Ho-rang.
I'll get going now. I'll see you tomorrow.

207
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:02,795
Okay.

208
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:10,095
[ I will explain myself. ]

209
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:21,645
Do you want to just give it to me
or what?

210
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:27,920
[ Search Account ]

211
00:10:23,980 --> 00:10:26,449
[ It's true.
They contacted me out of nowhere ]

212
00:10:26,450 --> 00:10:28,690
[ and said they'd tell me about
something you hate. ]

213
00:10:27,990 --> 00:10:29,560
[ Can't find the user ]

214
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:31,529
[ I've never seen that ID before either.
It's true. ]

215
00:10:31,530 --> 00:10:32,629
[ Friend. I have something to say. ]

216
00:10:32,630 --> 00:10:34,429
[ Lee Jung-won: Kim Sol-ji, I feel
troubled with mock exams coming up. ]

217
00:10:34,430 --> 00:10:35,955
[ Lee Tae-won: Hyun Ji-yeon,
Park Sun-hyung: Hong Ji-soo ]

218
00:10:42,370 --> 00:10:45,309
Ho-rang. Let's go to the new VR game room
after school today.

219
00:10:45,310 --> 00:10:48,375
If you put it on your feed, you'll
get a lot of likes, so you should...

220
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,579
I wanted to try that. Is it good?

221
00:10:51,580 --> 00:10:53,579
- Want a bite?
- Yes. Just a bite.

222
00:10:53,580 --> 00:10:54,815
Hurry up.

223
00:10:57,820 --> 00:11:00,349
Oh, she's my friend, Baek Ho-rang.

224
00:11:00,350 --> 00:11:03,189
- Ho-rang, say hi to them.
- Hello.

225
00:11:03,190 --> 00:11:05,829
Hey, Kim Yu-shin. Have fun.
I'm going to go first.

226
00:11:05,830 --> 00:11:07,895
Why? Let's go together.

227
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,065
Yes! We got some snacks. Let's eat them.

228
00:11:19,140 --> 00:11:20,465
Hey, Ko Eun-taek.

229
00:11:24,780 --> 00:11:26,675
Do you have some time?

230
00:11:38,130 --> 00:11:39,225
I'm sorry.

231
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:43,355
I'm apologizing.

232
00:11:45,130 --> 00:11:49,195
No matter how mad I was,
I shouldn't have done that.

233
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:50,439
Also,

234
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:53,539
I wasn't hurt at all by the harsh words
you said to me last time.

235
00:11:53,540 --> 00:11:55,635
It didn't bother me at all.

236
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:58,245
I never asked if you were okay.

237
00:11:59,380 --> 00:12:00,545
Oh, right.

238
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:04,619
I thought you might feel sorry.

239
00:12:04,620 --> 00:12:05,785
Not at all.

240
00:12:06,390 --> 00:12:09,955
I'm still reminded of what you did,
and it upsets me every hour.

241
00:12:15,430 --> 00:12:17,929
Okay. I was wrong.

242
00:12:17,930 --> 00:12:20,225
- So can you...
- Yes, you were wrong.

243
00:12:23,270 --> 00:12:27,105
It's true that I was wrong,

244
00:12:27,980 --> 00:12:31,475
but what about you? You probably
didn't do anything right either.

245
00:12:32,050 --> 00:12:34,745
Look. You're not sorry at all right now.

246
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,215
It's obvious.

247
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:40,345
No. I feel bad. I really do, but...

248
00:12:40,420 --> 00:12:42,659
Why were you the one to say
harsh things to me,

249
00:12:42,660 --> 00:12:44,755
but I'm the one who apologized first?

250
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:47,159
Is this why you wanted to talk?

251
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:49,759
It's true. The person
who gets upset every hour

252
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:51,765
is me, not you.

253
00:12:54,130 --> 00:12:55,999
- I'm going to go.
- Fine. Go.

