00:39:52,450 --> 00:39:55,445
What about yesterday?
Why didn't you call me?

768
00:39:55,790 --> 00:39:56,885
I was studying.

769
00:39:57,290 --> 00:39:59,055
Gosh.
You're acting like this until the end.

770
00:39:59,260 --> 00:40:01,655
Are you the only one who's annoyed?

771
00:40:01,660 --> 00:40:02,995
I'm annoyed too.

772
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:05,059
But why must I always be the one to
hold onto you

773
00:40:05,060 --> 00:40:06,669
and say something
for you to start talking?

774
00:40:06,670 --> 00:40:07,965
- You did.
- When?

775
00:40:08,130 --> 00:40:09,235
You did.

776
00:40:13,940 --> 00:40:15,035
Jae-yi.

777
00:40:17,410 --> 00:40:20,649
Not calling for one day isn't something
to get this mad about.

778
00:40:20,650 --> 00:40:23,515
I'm not acting like this
because you didn't call one day.

779
00:40:23,820 --> 00:40:25,819
And other people
usually talk to each other every day.

780
00:40:25,820 --> 00:40:27,245
It's just that you don't.

781
00:40:30,060 --> 00:40:32,515
Okay. I'm sorry.

782
00:40:35,330 --> 00:40:39,225
Do Woo-jae.
I've been dating you for two years,

783
00:40:39,500 --> 00:40:42,165
but there are times when I have no idea
what's on your mind.

784
00:40:43,240 --> 00:40:46,005
It feels like I'm putting on a show
by myself.

785
00:40:50,440 --> 00:40:51,605
Forget it.

786
00:40:52,110 --> 00:40:54,105
I'm the only one to suffer
if I get mad like this.

787
00:41:38,660 --> 00:41:42,660
[ Please wash hands with soap. ]

788
00:41:40,690 --> 00:41:42,995
Ko Eun-taek told me to start training you.

789
00:41:43,060 --> 00:41:44,995
- So later...
- Hey, Ji So-hyun.

790
00:41:47,470 --> 00:41:48,725
Are you...

791
00:41:55,740 --> 00:41:57,575
You're really irritating me.

792
00:42:01,880 --> 00:42:03,075
Thank goodness.

793
00:42:05,020 --> 00:42:06,715
I thought it was just me.

794
00:42:11,220 --> 00:42:14,355
Gosh. If you're done
washing your hands, move over!

795
00:42:14,760 --> 00:42:16,425
Move. My gosh.

796
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:21,195
Hey, Baek Ho-rang.

797
00:42:21,200 --> 00:42:23,965
You need to prepare for the presentation,
so what are you doing here?

798
00:42:24,540 --> 00:42:25,865
Why are you picking a fight?

799
00:42:26,440 --> 00:42:28,669
Yoo Si-eun
skipped the meeting yesterday too.

800
00:42:28,670 --> 00:42:30,679
Shouldn't we take her name out?

801
00:42:30,680 --> 00:42:32,675
Gosh, I'm so mad!

802
00:42:32,710 --> 00:42:35,975
You're mad because of Do Woo-jae,
not Yoo Si-eun.

803
00:42:36,250 --> 00:42:39,689
Why would I be mad because of Do Woo-jae?
I'm not.

804
00:42:39,690 --> 00:42:44,455
Why? You should've grabbed him by
the collar during gym and fought with him.

805
00:42:44,760 --> 00:42:46,989
Forget it. I don't know.
Hurry up and give me the USB.

806
00:42:46,990 --> 00:42:49,185
Why are you telling me to give it to you
in the bathroom?

807
00:42:49,530 --> 00:42:50,695
Follow me.

808
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:52,995
I'm following you out right now.

809
00:42:53,170 --> 00:42:55,765
[ Be quiet.
Keep your distance as you follow me. ]

810
00:43:05,710 --> 00:43:06,779
[ Har Ley ]

811
00:43:06,780 --> 00:43:08,575
[ Ji So-hyun ]

812
00:43:14,490 --> 00:43:16,955
[ Lee Seon-ju ]

813
00:43:17,990 --> 00:43:19,085
[ Lee Seon-ju ]

814
00:43:35,310 --> 00:43:36,475
So-hyun.

815
00:43:38,180 --> 00:43:39,979
Is the place
you got hit by Baek Ho-rang okay?

816
00:43:39,980 --> 00:43:41,949
I begged the nurse to give me all of this,

817
00:43:41,950 --> 00:43:43,675
so make sure you use it. Okay?

818
00:43:43,780 --> 00:43:45,045
I'm fine.

819
00:43:45,250 --> 00:43:46,319
Thank you.

820
00:43:46,320 --> 00:43:48,389
Baek Ho-rang needs to do something
about her temper.

821
00:43:48,390 --> 00:43:50,059
She was complaining about
how she didn't want to do it,

822
00:43:50,060 --> 00:43:51,515
but she was the worst out of everyone.

823
00:43:51,620 --> 00:43:55,089
So-hyun. Even if it doesn't hurt now,
it might hurt later. So...

824
00:43:55,090 --> 00:43:56,995
- Yu-shin.
- Yes?

825
00:43:57,230 --> 00:44:00,025
I'm really okay, so can you go?

826
00:44:00,070 --> 00:44:01,725
I need to get ready for class.

827
00:44:01,730 --> 00:44:03,595
I see. Okay.

828
00:44:03,770 --> 00:44:05,769
I wasted your time, didn't I?

829
00:44:05,770 --> 00:44:08,165
I'll come back next time.
Have fun in class, So-hyun.

830
00:44:18,420 --> 00:44:21,420
[ Please listen. ]

831
00:44:18,480 --> 00:44:21,585
[ You need a proper solution
to your problem. ]

832
00:44:21,750 --> 00:44:25,289
[ Anyone can become the assailant
and the victim. ]

833
00:44:25,290 --> 00:44:26,485
I'll go in now.

834
00:44:26,690 --> 00:44:27,785
Okay.

835
00:44:29,260 --> 00:44:31,929
Baek Ho-rang.
Go in with her and watch her.

836
00:44:31,930 --> 00:44:33,025
What?

837
00:44:34,430 --> 00:44:37,199
No. It's not even the lunch broadcast.

838
00:44:37,200 --> 00:44:38,935
Take the script on the table with you.

839
00:44:40,970 --> 00:44:42,235
My gosh.

840
00:44:47,480 --> 00:44:48,950
You just need to read what's written.

841
00:44:47,980 --> 00:44:49,720
[ School Violence Prevention
Education Broadcast ]

842
00:44:49,010 --> 00:44:52,279
After you're done reading, be sure to turn
off the mic so your voice doesn't go out.

843
00:44:52,280 --> 00:44:54,115
Then give Eun-taek the sign.

844
00:44:54,790 --> 00:44:56,189
[ You have ten seconds. Get ready. ]

845
00:44:56,190 --> 00:44:57,385
And...

846
00:44:58,520 --> 00:44:59,725
Focus.

847
00:45:00,360 --> 00:45:02,289
Don't make others suffer
from your mistakes.

848
00:45:02,290 --> 00:45:03,395
[ Five seconds. ]

849
00:45:06,670 --> 00:45:08,465
May I please have your attention?

850
00:45:09,370 --> 00:45:12,739
The school violence prevention education
broadcast will start soon,

851
00:45:12,740 --> 00:45:15,465
so please turn on the TV
in your classroom and wait.

852
00:45:15,470 --> 00:45:17,235
I repeat.

853
00:45:17,480 --> 00:45:20,675
[ The school violence prevention education
broadcast will start soon, ]

854
00:45:20,680 --> 00:45:23,445
[ so please turn on the TV
in your classroom and wait. ]

855
00:45:24,820 --> 00:45:28,915
[ The first step in preventing
school violence is paying attention. ]

856
00:45:29,190 --> 00:45:31,319
[ If you have been a victim of violence ]

857
00:45:31,320 --> 00:45:32,989
[ or you have seen it happen, ]

858
00:45:32,990 --> 00:45:36,899
[ you must ask a teacher or your parents
for help. ]

859
00:45:36,900 --> 00:45:39,629
[ If you hide this fact
because you are afraid, ]

860
00:45:39,630 --> 00:45:41,765
[ you can't help anyone. ]

861
00:45:41,900 --> 00:45:44,495
[ If you don't say anything,
nobody will know. ]

862
00:45:47,340 --> 00:45:50,480
[ Kang Jae-yi ]

863
00:45:47,610 --> 00:45:49,905
[ Jae-yi. Later... ]

864
00:45:52,180 --> 00:45:54,175
[ Jae-yi. Later... ]

865
00:45:56,580 --> 00:45:58,745
[ The courage to tell
the people around you. ]

866
00:45:58,950 --> 00:46:00,545
[ The courage not to be a spectator. ]

867
00:46:01,090 --> 00:46:03,155
[ That's the key. ]

868
00:46:10,160 --> 00:46:12,929
If something ever happens, don't hesitate.

869
00:46:12,930 --> 00:46:15,269
Tell me or our teacher, okay?

870
00:46:15,270 --> 00:46:16,435
Kim Yu-shin.

871
00:46:16,500 --> 00:46:18,299
You're the one who should watch out
for bullies.

872
00:46:18,300 --> 00:46:20,069
You can mind your own business.

873
00:46:20,070 --> 00:46:22,605
All right. But tell me
if anything goes wrong, okay?

874
00:46:23,710 --> 00:46:26,579
[ Therefore, in order to prevent bullying, ]

875
00:46:26,580 --> 00:46:29,109
[ continuous conversation
with your friend is needed, ]

876
00:46:29,110 --> 00:46:32,345
[ as well as a proper solution
to work problems out. ]

877
00:46:32,420 --> 00:46:36,615
[ Anyone can become the assailant
and the victim. ]

878
00:46:37,090 --> 00:46:39,389
[ - Hope begins with you. ]
- The microphone is on.

879
00:46:39,390 --> 00:46:42,285
[ What kind of a person
do you want to be? ]

880
00:46:42,360 --> 00:46:44,159
That was Ms. Kim So-young

881
00:46:44,160 --> 00:46:46,429
from the Green Tree Foundation
on bullying.

882
00:46:46,430 --> 00:46:48,329
Do we have a meeting tomorrow morning?

883
00:46:48,330 --> 00:46:50,369
No, we don't. See you all at lunch.

884
00:46:50,370 --> 00:46:52,339
- Good work.
- Thank you for your hard work.

885
00:46:52,340 --> 00:46:53,805
- See you tomorrow.
- Bye!

886
00:46:56,740 --> 00:46:58,775
Can Ho-rang start from tomorrow?

887
00:47:00,110 --> 00:47:01,205
Yes.

888
00:47:01,510 --> 00:47:03,215
- See you tomorrow.
- All right.

889
00:47:10,760 --> 00:47:12,485
Why are you still here?

890
00:47:17,100 --> 00:47:19,429
What was that about?
What about So-hyun?

891
00:47:19,430 --> 00:47:22,065
- Training you.
- Training?

892
00:47:22,130 --> 00:47:23,565
Is that necessary?

893
00:47:23,900 --> 00:47:25,669
Do you know what you have to do
as the anchor?

894
00:47:25,670 --> 00:47:28,635
I just need to read whatever is written
on the script.

895
00:47:28,840 --> 00:47:30,709
Learn well from So-hyun tomorrow.

896
00:47:30,710 --> 00:47:32,239
I'm going to make you go
on your own soon.

897
00:47:32,240 --> 00:47:33,749
Darn it.

898
00:47:33,750 --> 00:47:35,179
You can train me instead.

899
00:47:35,180 --> 00:47:36,679
I don't want to talk to So-hyun.

900
00:47:36,680 --> 00:47:39,915
The team isn't a joke.
You don't get to do whatever you want.

901
00:47:42,050 --> 00:47:44,959
Why? She's fine with training you.

902
00:47:44,960 --> 00:47:46,255
Are you not okay with it?

903
00:47:46,660 --> 00:47:47,789
Has she talked about me?

904
00:47:47,790 --> 00:47:50,655
She just said that she knows you
from middle school.

905
00:47:51,200 --> 00:47:52,199
Whatever.

906
00:47:52,200 --> 00:47:54,929
You train me, okay?

907
00:47:54,930 --> 00:47:57,469
- I'll think about it.
- "I'll think about it"?

908
00:47:57,470 --> 00:47:59,609
I'm not going to do it
if you're not training.

909
00:47:59,610 --> 00:48:01,339
- You can go now.
- I'm serious.

910
00:48:01,340 --> 00:48:03,605
All right. I said I'll think about it.

911
00:48:04,780 --> 00:48:07,475
- Aren't you going home?
- I'm going to work on this first.

912
00:48:07,510 --> 00:48:08,605
Okay, then.

913
00:48:11,150 --> 00:48:14,445
Why do you carry this around?

914
00:48:14,920 --> 00:48:16,285
For you to see it.

915
00:48:16,420 --> 00:48:18,289
How petty.

916
00:48:18,290 --> 00:48:20,585
I won't forget.

917
00:48:21,090 --> 00:48:23,425
I'm just kidding.
I'm going to get it later.

918
00:48:24,330 --> 00:48:26,725
We can go together then.

919
00:48:27,430 --> 00:48:29,525
To where? To the record shop?

920
00:48:29,530 --> 00:48:31,339
Yes. If I let you be,

921
00:48:31,340 --> 00:48:34,069
that's all you're
ever going to talk about.

922
00:48:34,070 --> 00:48:36,609
I don't want to hear any of it,
so let's go right now.

923
00:48:36,610 --> 00:48:37,775
I'll buy it for you.

924
00:48:39,850 --> 00:48:42,505
What are you waiting for? Let's go!

925
00:48:48,420 --> 00:48:49,985
[ "When My Loneliness Calls You" ]

926
00:49:16,380 --> 00:49:18,145
What is it? Are there no seats?

927
00:49:18,350 --> 00:49:19,715
There's a seat over there.

928
00:49:23,160 --> 00:49:25,659
Hello.

929
00:49:25,660 --> 00:49:26,955
- Hello.
- Hello.

930
00:49:27,160 --> 00:49:29,429
The September exam is

931
00:49:29,430 --> 00:49:31,429
- coming up quite fast.
- Yes.

932
00:49:31,430 --> 00:49:34,599
But what's our ultimate goal?
The College Scholastic Ability Test.

933
00:49:34,600 --> 00:49:37,339
Today, we're going to...

934
00:49:37,340 --> 00:49:40,139
[ Were you the one who moved
my backpack? ]

935
00:49:40,140 --> 00:49:41,509
Please highlight this part.

936
00:49:41,510 --> 00:49:43,809
Remember that...

937
00:49:43,810 --> 00:49:44,875
Why?

938
00:49:45,080 --> 00:49:47,205
Because I wanted you to sit next to me.

939
00:49:50,050 --> 00:49:51,945
Why are you mad?

940
00:49:52,780 --> 00:49:55,785
It's nothing like that. I was just tired.

941
00:49:56,760 --> 00:49:57,855
I'm sorry.

942
00:49:58,660 --> 00:50:00,355
Are you sick?

943
00:50:00,830 --> 00:50:01,955
No.

944
00:50:04,160 --> 00:50:05,429
Jae-yi,

945
00:50:05,430 --> 00:50:07,495
do you want to catch
a night movie with me later?

946
00:50:09,670 --> 00:50:10,795
Why don't we?

947
00:50:10,940 --> 00:50:12,595
Have you watched "Hero"?

948
00:50:12,670 --> 00:50:15,465
I've been wanting to watch it,
but I haven't had the chance to.

949
00:50:16,370 --> 00:50:18,305
Who else would I watch it with?

950
00:50:20,280 --> 00:50:22,979
I also want to watch "The Reporter".
Let's watch that tomorrow.

951
00:50:22,980 --> 00:50:24,415
Be quiet in the back.

952
00:50:26,050 --> 00:50:29,645
So, it wouldn't be R...

953
00:50:30,090 --> 00:50:32,385
- Let's watch that too.
- Sounds great.

954
00:50:38,960 --> 00:50:42,099
- This is that, right?
- Yes, it is.

955
00:50:42,100 --> 00:50:43,265
Can I take this?

956
00:50:44,770 --> 00:50:46,539
No, what's the most expensive one here?

957
00:50:46,540 --> 00:50:48,465
This is the most expensive one.

958
00:50:48,470 --> 00:50:50,179
It was just released this week.

959
00:50:50,180 --> 00:50:51,379
I'll take it then.

960
00:50:51,380 --> 00:50:53,679
Okay. I'll get you a new one at the front.

961
00:50:53,680 --> 00:50:54,805
Thank you.

962
00:51:03,290 --> 00:51:05,815
Seems like they have everything
to suit your old-fashioned taste here.

963
00:51:07,190 --> 00:51:09,229
How many times do I need to tell you
that it's analog?

964
00:51:09,230 --> 00:51:10,729
I found it!

965
00:51:10,730 --> 00:51:12,155
[ "When My Loneliness Calls You" ]

966
00:51:19,570 --> 00:51:20,735
Give it a listen.

967
00:51:22,270 --> 00:51:23,905
This is so old.

968
00:52:16,760 --> 00:52:18,795
What do you think? Isn't it good?

969
00:52:19,360 --> 00:52:20,999
You can just find the song online.

970
00:52:21,000 --> 00:52:23,225
Why come all the way here to buy this?

971
00:52:24,370 --> 00:52:25,695
It's exciting.

972
00:52:27,070 --> 00:52:29,205
The ordering, the waiting,

973
00:52:29,540 --> 00:52:31,735
and coming here to pick it up.

974
00:52:39,420 --> 00:52:41,585
I really don't get it.

975
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:46,115
The speaker is ready.

976
00:52:46,490 --> 00:52:47,585
- Okay.
- Okay.

977
00:52:49,030 --> 00:52:51,425
You're buying this, right? Give it to me.

978
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:54,365
- I already have.
- When?

979
00:52:54,430 --> 00:52:55,825
When you were doing something else.

980
00:52:56,030 --> 00:52:57,265
Pay for your order.

981
00:52:57,940 --> 00:53:00,165
What? I thought you wanted me
to pay you back.

982
00:53:14,120 --> 00:53:16,685
[ Aron Book ]

983
00:53:16,760 --> 00:53:17,855
Here.

984
00:53:18,920 --> 00:53:20,025
For me?

985
00:53:20,760 --> 00:53:22,729
I don't even have a turntable.

986
00:53:22,730 --> 00:53:25,525
I know you love things that look fancy.

987
00:53:27,170 --> 00:53:29,225
It's pretty, so put it somewhere
in your room.

988
00:53:30,040 --> 00:53:32,235
Sure, then.

989
00:53:37,310 --> 00:53:39,840
[ Father ]

990
00:53:37,510 --> 00:53:39,605
[ I'm going home right now.
When will you be home? ]

991
00:53:44,150 --> 00:53:46,375
- Ho-rang,
- Yes?

992
00:53:47,120 --> 00:53:48,689
since I bought the record for you...

993
00:53:48,690 --> 00:53:50,089
I knew it!

994
00:53:50,090 --> 00:53:52,419
This is why I was going to pay...

995
00:53:52,420 --> 00:53:53,525
Eat with me.

996
00:53:55,690 --> 00:53:57,025
You can pay for the meal.

997
00:54:19,880 --> 00:54:21,445
Is this really good enough for a meal?

998
00:54:21,890 --> 00:54:23,515
It's too much of a hassle to go far.

999
00:54:24,160 --> 00:54:25,555
We can order something.

1000
00:54:25,620 --> 00:54:28,155
If you feel bad, buy me something good
next time.

1001
00:54:28,230 --> 00:54:30,795
What do you mean? Once is enough.

1002
00:54:43,880 --> 00:54:45,635
Is something wrong?

1003
00:54:46,140 --> 00:54:47,245
No.

1004
00:54:47,910 --> 00:54:49,475
Why do you keep checking your watch then?

1005
00:54:49,550 --> 00:54:51,249
I have to be home before 11 p.m.

1006
00:54:51,250 --> 00:54:52,375
Why?

1007
00:54:53,120 --> 00:54:55,045
That's a rule I set for myself.

1008
00:54:55,890 --> 00:54:57,215
So, why?

1009
00:55:02,660 --> 00:55:05,299
Here's what I noticed about you
when I first met you.

1010
00:55:05,300 --> 00:55:07,265
Why do you obsess over time?

1011
00:55:07,370 --> 00:55:09,495
You plan your schedule by minutes.

1012
00:55:10,540 --> 00:55:14,005
Are you trying to become
a perfectionist or something?

1013
00:55:16,410 --> 00:55:17,705
No.

1014
00:55:20,280 --> 00:55:22,505
You're living a difficult life too.

1015
00:55:24,380 --> 00:55:25,775
I want to keep them.

1016
00:55:30,220 --> 00:55:31,315
Keep what?

1017
00:55:31,790 --> 00:55:32,885
Promises.

1018
00:55:36,590 --> 00:55:40,325
I hate people who don't keep
their promises and who lie to me.

1019
00:55:42,530 --> 00:55:44,095
They might not realize it,

1020
00:55:44,200 --> 00:55:46,665
but breaking promises and lying
can hurt other people.

1021
00:55:52,880 --> 00:55:54,705
I guess you have nothing to hide.

1022
